body:
After having put more thought into the issue, I figured I could demonstrate the problem in a much simpler fashion.

```java
package example;

// imports ...

class NestedExecutionOrderTests {

	@Test
	void test1() {
		System.out.println("test 1");
	}

	@Nested
	class NestedTests {

		@Test
		void test2() {
			System.out.println("test 2");
		}

		@Nested
		class DoubleNestedTests {

			@Test
			void test3() {
				System.out.println("test 3");
			}
		}
	}
}
```

Running that standalone results in:

```
test 1
test 2
test 3
```

Select all test classes (including nested test classes) via classpath scanning like this:

```java
@Suite
@SelectPackages("example")
class NestedTestsSuite {
}
```

Running that suite results in:

```
test 3
test 2
test 1
```

Thus, the tests are executed in inverted order, and I've updated the title of this issue to reflect that.
